Ingredients.1: 1 (10 ounce) can Old El Paso® Red Enchilada Sauce

Ingredients.4: 1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese, cut into 1/2-inch cubes

Ingredients.6: 10  Old El Paso® flour tortillas for soft tacos & fajitas (6 inch)

Directions.1: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Spray a 13x9-inch baking dish with cooking spray. Spread 1/4 cup of enchilada sauce in the bottom of the baking dish.

Directions.2: Mix chicken, 1 cup of Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, and seasoning mix in a medium bowl; spoon slightly less than 1/2 cup of filling onto each tortilla. Roll up each tortilla tightly; place seam-side down in the prepared baking dish. Drizzle with remaining enchilada sauce. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese on top; cover with foil.

Directions.3: Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes; uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until bubbly and lightly browned.
